text.section:
A member of the Employees' Retirement System may purchase service credit for a period of employment:
not exceeding 10 years of out-of-state public school teaching service;
not exceeding 10 years for public or nonpublic school teaching service;
not exceeding 5 years for postsecondary school teaching service;
not exceeding 10 years of federal service or out-of-state service with a political subdivision; or
as an employee of a political subdivision of the State if:
the member is not otherwise entitled to receive service credit for the same period under this Division II;
the member is not receiving retirement benefits from a political subdivision of the State for the same period; and
the member, the political subdivision, or both, pay the amount required under subsection (b)(1) of this section.

A member of the Teachers' Retirement System may purchase service credit for a period of employment:
not exceeding 10 years of out-of-state public school teaching service;
not exceeding 10 years of public or nonpublic school teaching service;
not exceeding 5 years of postsecondary school teaching service;
on or before December 31, 1970, with Baltimore City as a teacher on a verified leave of absence not exceeding 2 years that is similar in all respects to leaves of absence approved by the Board of Trustees;
not exceeding 10 years of federal or out-of-state municipal service; or
employment as an employee of a municipal corporation of the State if the member is not otherwise entitled to receive service credit under this Division II.
